      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a constitutional doctrine that protects fundamental rights and liberties by allowing the judiciary to strike down laws that infringe upon them, even without explicit text in the Constitution. This tool has been instrumental in advancing civil rights by safeguarding privacy, gender equality, and freedom of conscience against government overreach. By empowering courts to define these rights based on evolving societal standards, substantive due process ensures that individual liberties remain robust and adaptable to changing times.",
